<h1><font color="<TMPL_VAR NAME="link_color">">page</font>kit.org: Website for Apache::PageKit</h1>

PageKit<SUP>TM</SUP> is an <a href="http://perl.apache.org">mod_perl</a> based
application framework that uses HTML::Template and XML to
separate the design from the content.  Includes session management,
authentication, form validation, co-branding, and a content
management system.
<p>
Documentation and downloads are available from
<a href="http://search.cpan.org/search?dist=Apache-PageKit">CPAN</a>.
<p>
To browse the <a href="http://sourceforge.net/cvs/?group_id=9597">CVS</a> or join a 
<a href="http://sourceforge.net/mail/?group_id=9597">mailing list</a>, visit
<a href="http://sourceforge.net/projects/pagekit/">Sourceforge</a>.
<p>
For PageKit services, including commercial support, contact <a href="mailto:pagekit@anidea.com">pagekit@thoughtstore.com</a>.
<p>
This site serves as a demo of some of the features of PageKit.  The complete source
code for pagekit.org is located in the eg/ directory of the distribution.
